data.name: ObtainingDamageFileLabel2.Text
data.value: Open "pakchunk0-WindowsNoEditor.pak" Inside of "APK/Content/MasterData/Plc"contains various character folders. You'll have to find the one you want to modify. Inside of one of these folders is "<charid>prm_damage.uasset" Right click on the .uasset and select: Export Raw Data Now inside of your Output folder, the pathway to this file exists.

data.name: ApplyChangesLabel2.Text
data.value: Drag the modname folder into "UnrealPak-With-Compression.bat" to generate a .pak Inside of your Paks folder ("Demon Slayer\APK\Content\Paks\"), create a new folder called "~mods" Insert the .pak into the "~mods" folder.

data.name: EventLabel.Text
data.value:
Two DataTable Entries cannot have the same name. However as long as that isn't the case, I believe you can name them anything. This tool should automatically make sure that no two entries are the same.
All Timing values must go in order. -1 is used for when the animation ends. If it suddenly skips to like 500, then a function before it likely forced to skip to that point.
Example: If you have a Animation ID with 3 Events and the Timings are like: 0, 3, 0. The game will end up breaking, so you'll need to move that entry so it looks like this: 0, 0, 3.
The DataTable Entries with the same Animation ID do NOT have to be next to each other, but they all are in vanilla files. Just keep in mind that they do need to be in Timing order.
I left in the ability to add your own Animation IDs via typing in the drop down list however this is not advised. Since they are a Object ENum, they all are hardcoded inside the .exe so if you use one that does not exist, it may either just not work or outright crash the game. I left this in as future proofing incase the game updates with new EAnimationIds.
When adding or removing DataTable Entries to the Event File, you'll have to edit one of the prm_mot files. The Additional prm_mot files each have one Table Entry that says how many Event Functions a single Event has. It does not seem like it matters where you put new Animation ID DataTable Entries.
It is currently unknown what a majority of Functions do or how they're used. The Function List was dumped via Cheat Engine through some pure luck so we can have a good idea of what we're messing with.
Argument Int 1-3 (ArgN# in UAssetGUI) are parameters that only use whole numbers. Argument Float 1-6 (ArgF) are parameters that can use decimals. Coordinate Name is used for string like IDs, like saying which Hitbox to use, which Damage ID to load, which cancel codes to use, ect. I have not seen the DamageID nor the EndureID used a single time yet but still decided to add them just incase.
